The investigators have shown that a single dose of ultraviolet irradiation (as found in sunlight) will lower blood pressure for around one hour.

 They are now testing whether daily UVA for two weeks will produce a sustained fall in BP in patients with high blood pressure.

 They will also measure the effect of daily UVA on other cardiovascular risk factors.

